For compatibility with older compilers, the Roslyn C# compiler permits the following method without a diagnostic

``` c#
    void M<T>(T t)
    {
        lock (t) // error? warning?
        {
        }
    }
```

In "strict" mode we produce an error that the lock statement requires a reference type.

Consider adding a warning or error in a warning wave for this situation.

